 {}}, "fastFollowersCount": 0, "favouritesCount": 12492, "hasCustomTimelines": true, "isTranslator": false, "mediaCount": 6242, "statusesCount": 29818, "withheldInCountries": [], "affiliatesHighlightedLabel": {}, "possiblySensitive": false, "pinnedTweetIds": ["1936425917016092887"], "profile_bio": {"description": "Full Time Technical Analyst & Investor | This is not financial advice", "entities": {"description": {}, "url": {"urls": [{"display_url": "patreon.com/TheValueTrader", "expanded_url": "http://patreon.com/TheValueTrader", "indices": [0, 23], "url": "https://t.co/1pcejo5FVo"}]}}}, "isAutomated": false, "automatedBy": null}, "extendedEntities": {}, "card": null, "place": {}, "entities": {"hashtags": [], "symbols": [{"indices": [13, 18], "text": "BIDU"}], "timestamps": [], "urls": [], "user_mentions": []}, "quoted_tweet": null, "retweeted_tweet": null, "isLimitedReply": false, "communityInfo": null, "article": null}], "dropped": [{"reason": "cashtags=5", "tweet": {"type": "tweet", "id": "2049566391595094453", "url": "https://x.com/TheValueTrade/status/2049566391595094453", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/TheValueTrade/status/2049566391595094453", "text": "$BIDU\n\nFirst of all, apologies for the long post.\n\nRight now on the chart we can see $BIDU is currently testing the confluence of the 50-day and 200-day MAs at $120, if the price can hold above this level, then we can begin looking at the resistance that will come from the top of Wave 1 at $165.\n\nBreak above $165 would remove any concerns of a deeper pullback, and would confirm we are in Wave 3, with a target at the 1.618 Fib at $252.\n\nThe downside risk here, is if the 2 MAs fail to hold for support, then the 0.786 Fib at $94 would likely come into play.\n\nNow I want to share my view on thefundamentals, because this is where things get very interesting.\n\n$BIDU is currently trading with a market cap around $41B. At the same time, Waymo\u2019s last private valuation came in around $126B.... Just for a comparison.\n\nLet that sink in.\n\nThe market is effectively valuing ALL of Baidu, search, cloud, AI, Apollo autonomous driving, ERNIE models, and cash at roughly one third of Waymo alone.\n\nEven more important, $BIDU has a very strong balance sheet...... With roughly $20B+ in net cash and investments, a huge portion of the current valuation is backed by cash.... Which is just insane!\n\nThis is where the asymmetric opportunity comes in -\n\nProfitable core search business\n\nGrowing cloud segment\n\nStrong AI positioning with ERNIE\n\nAutonomous driving through Apollo\n\nLarge net cash position\n\nWhen you break it down further -\n\nSearch: $5.5B\n\nCloud: $12.9B\n\nApollo: $2.9B\n\nKunlun AI Chip: $17B\n\nNet cash: $19.3B\n\niQIYI: $761M\n\nTotal estimated value comes out around $170 per share vs where it trades today at $120ish...\n\nThe cash alone is massive...\n\nLooking at the valuation metrics -\n\nP/E: 80.65 (distorted by accounting/one-offs)\n\nForward P/E: 13.28\n\nPEG: 1.14\n\nP/S: 1.88\n\nP/B: 1.08\n\nEV/EBITDA: 13.44\n\nThis is not the profile of an overvalued company. If anything, it reinforces the idea that the market is heavily discounting future growth and optionality.\n\nFor me, this is what makes $BIDU so attractive at these levels...\n\nYou have a technically defined setup with clear invalidation and upside targets, combined with a fundamentally undervalued business that has multiple growth levers.\n\nIn my opinion, this is one of those positions where the numbers are hard to ignore or even impossible to ignore.\n\nAt some point, the market will start pricing this correctly.\n\nAnd when it does, it won\u2019t happen slowly.\n\nAnd yes, I did see on the news about the 100 cars that stalled... For me this is a complete overreaction.", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 1, "replyCount": 3, "likeCount": 22, "quoteCount": 0, "viewCount": 4236, "createdAt": "Wed Apr 29 19:08:01 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 5, "isReply"